D. Acquisition Strategy
The program is pursuing a single Middle Tier of Acquisition for Rapid Prototyping (MTA-RP) pathway with a decision point informed by an operational assessment
NLT 4QFY28 to transition to a Middle Tier of Acquisition for Rapid Fielding (MTA-RF) upon successful demonstration of technical maturity. As of February 2026, the
program is pursuing a fair and open competition with the intent of awarding up to six Other Transaction Authority for Prototyping (OTAP) award(s) for rapid prototyping.
This strategy leverages existing Army munitions and fire control systems while prioritizing but not limited to commercial mobility platforms and autonomy solutions.
Additionally, the program will initiate the development of Common Onboard Launcher Electronics (COLE). The program will deliver:
* Develop up to 8 complete system prototypes and 1 spare MP that fire the TLAM
* Develop 1 complete system prototype that fires the PAC3/MSE
* Develop 1 complete system prototype that fires MFOM
* Develop 1 complete system prototype that fires IFPC
* Develop 1 spare AMP to be used as a test asset
Prototypes must be ready for an operational assessment NLT 4QFY28
The CAML Abbreviated Capability Development Document (A-CDD) was approved at the Army Requirements Oversight Council (AROC) in May 2025, demonstrating
alignment with Army priorities.




