A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This program element provides funding for the development of systems that fulfill a portion of the third phase of the Ship Self Defense: Engage Hard Kill. Development in
this line will focus on hard kill capabilities in which missiles and other munitions are used to intercept incoming Anti-Ship Cruise Missiles (ASCM), as well as a Surface-to
Surface Strike weapon system. System improvements are being addressed via Rolling Airframe Missile (RAM) (0167), NATO SEASPARROW Missile System (NSSMS)
(0173), Over-The-Horizon (OTH) missile (2070), Afloat Counter-Unmanned Aerial Systems (C-UAS) (2077), and MK-15 Close-In Weapon System (CIWS) (9081).

