       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $1.694 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

       FY 2024: The change from the previous President's Budget includes a decrease due to Small Business Innovation Research and Small Business Technology
       Transfer (SBIR/STTR) $1.616 million and an increase of $0.858 million to support Naval Strike Missile (NSM) on DDGs.

       FY 2025: The change from the previous President's Budget includes two Congressionally directed reductions (NGLS excess to need and ESSM integration and
       test ahead of need).

       FY 2026: The change from the previous President's Budget includes -$2.141 million in rate and misc adjustments.

       Proj 0173 NATO Sea Sparrow: The total change of +$19.513 million from the previous President's Budget in FY 2026 is due to an increase to support the
       Adaptable Deck Launcher (ADL) program for live fire testing, Combat System Final Qualification Testing (FQT), completion and delivery of prototype assets, and
       delivery of the Level 3 technical data package (TDP). Additionally in the FY the program will conduct testing at SCSC Wallops Island to complete final qualification
       testing (FQT) of the Adaptable Deck Launcher (ADL) system software as well as Combat system integration FQT testing with the Ship Self Defense System
       (SSDS). In parallel the program will conduct live fire testing of the prototype which is to include 2 events. One of the required events is to perform a restrained
       firing event to validate the plenum and its design, validate the analyses for ambient cell temp, and validate analysis for the overall structures ability to withstand
       a restrained firing. The second test required during this period is to conduct a firing of a Blast Test Vehicle (BTV) to validate egress analyses of an Evolved
       Seasparrow firing out of a MK25 quad pack canister at the new launch angle of 20 degrees. The program will also be processing and working logistics documents
       to include but not limited to installation manuals, technical manuals and instructions, and user maintenance procedures.

       Proj 2077 Afloat C-UAS: The total change of +$39.467 million from the previous President's Budget in FY 2026 is due to the addition of the Afloat Counter-
       Unmanned Aerial Systems (Afloat C-UAS) project which provides cost-effective shipboard capability against Unmanned Aerial Systems (UAS) with defeat options
       such as missiles, loitering munitions, and surface ship guns.




