launcher SW development to support Uplink/Downlink HW new development items.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
Continue integration efforts of the RAM Guided Missile Weapon System (GMWS) into the SSDS BL12 and Aegis
Combat Systems which will provide full RAM Block 2B capabilities to the fleet. Integration efforts include RAM
engineering support to review combat system architecture, documentation and design in addition to assisting
combat system designers with their understanding and interpretation of the RAM Weapon Specifications and
Guidelines for Effective Use. FY 2026 major effort is support SSDS BL 12 Integration, Development Test
(DT) and Operational Test (OT) events on Ship Self Defense Test Ship (SDTS) and Combat System Ship
Qualification Test (CSSQT) on lead ship. Support of AEGIS BL 9.C3.x CS integration.

Continue the RAM "Performance Lab" to provide quick turnaround raid performance curves which guide
integration, tactics, and future investments decisions, including software improvement decisions. Continue to
conduct experiments to verify the modeling and simulation indicating performance improvements are grounded
in actual testing. The major efforts are a continuation of the analysis of backlogged Red Sea engagement data
to inform software improvements for the RAM Software Factory and conduct a flight test with SW 7.10. The flight
test will verify the performance improvements implemented and provide an opportunity for further learning.

Continue Software Factory efforts to deliver software performance updates incorporating improvements
identified through trade studies and flight tests. Develop and release two RAM Block 2B missile software
updates SW 7.10 and SW 7.11.



