 8. Adaptable Deck Launcher (ADL) (formerly Next Generation Launching System (NGLS): The purpose of the ADL effort is to develop, qualify, test, and integrate a
 replacement to the 50+ year old legacy MK 29 Guided Missile Launching System (GMLS) for large deck, capital warships including CVNs, LHAs, and LHDs. ADL will
 double ESSM capacity over the current MK 29 GMLS while maintaining current shipboard locations. The new launching system will allow significantly more flexibility for
 ESSM Block 1 and 2 in different loadout configurations with available inventory. This replacement will improve environmental protection for Guided Missile Assemblies
 (GMA) (reducing corrosion), reduce manning requirements for loading/unloading operations, mitigates long term supportability issues, addresses obsolescence, reduce
 the life cycle costs, and reduce the cost and time for ESSM in-service refurbishment or re-certification. The ADL replacement contains design margin to allow for ESSM
 evolutionary growth within the MK25 canister. The MK 29 GMLS capacity is limited for ESSM Block 2 deployment.

