FY 2025 Plans:
Starts the execution of the ESSM Block 2 IOT&E Phase 2 testing period with Developmental Testing (DT) to
include flight tests and WITs on the planned firing ship(s). IOT&E Phase 2 are prerequisites to support Full
Operational Capability (FOC) and Full Rate Production (FRP) milestones for ESSM Block 2.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
Enterprise testing starts in FY 2026 using both ESSM Block 1 and 2. Waterfront Integration Testing (WIT) will
be planned and conducted on the Self Defense Test Ship, CVN 79, and LHA 8 (using the MK-29 Min Mod
configuration) as well as DT/OT live fire events supporting both platform level and combat system level testing.
Aegis BL 10 testing continues with multiple events. ESSM Block 2 IOT&E Phase 2 will be started on Arleigh
Burke Class DDGs in FY26. Testing will include WIT and multiple live fire events on multiple platforms. A total of
12 targets, with modifications, to include range support will be procured to support these events. Threat model
development also occurs in FY26 to be included in lethality assessment required by DOT&E.
