Note
The FY 2027 request for Hypersonics includes $82,939 thousand of discretionary and $40,000 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $122,939 thousand.
The mandatory funding resources Hypersonics which is to support the development and test of the Blackbeard - Ground Launch (GL) low-cost hypersonic strike missile.
This effort will assess the potential to achieve a significantly reduced cost for high-speed strike capability complementing existing Precision Strike Missile (PrSM)
capabilities.

Budget transitions from Project HX3: All Up Round Canister (AUR+C) in FY 2026to Budget Project DP1: HIMARS Extended Range Demo (HERD) in FY 2027 to support
completion of the Blackbeard - Ground Launch (GL) advanced strike missile Minimum Viable Product (MVP).

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
The work in this Program Element (PE) supports development, system flight tests, software validation, and full integration into the High Mobility Artillery Rocket System
(HIMARS) platform, significantly expanding HIMARS lethality.

PE 0604182A/Project HX3, All Up Round and Canister (AUR+C), completed its funding cycle in FY 2026 with the full integration of the AUR+C into the High Mobility
Artillery Rocket System (HIMARS) platform. Efforts are now focused under Budget Project DP1: HIMARS Extended Range Demo (HERD) which will drive the program
through Engineering, Development, Testing, and Fielding. The HERD project supports the Army's Long Range Precision Fires (LRPF) modernization priority by
demonstrating the feasibility and performance of integrating a qualified, extended-range Blackbeard - Ground Launch (GL) advanced strike missile into the HIMARS
launcher system. This demonstration will assess the potential to achieve a significantly reduced cost for high-speed strike capability complementing existing Precision
Strike Missile (PrSM) capabilities.




