$$, $$090d3a095d4d1750b1f7409bb429697ddae35a6e43749e755c7e6d9aba56aec4$$, $${"A": "fca333204c541834a70ca533809c39cdc16f46fb768067bd5903460d16e76ff6", "C": "e499dec2e59f679490349b3a1dde291b28bd120493365813de525e4d1d3a6328", "D": "a4a790e6f3fb00238931710b1355446518d257403feba1bb26a9989bcd295196"}$$::jsonb, $$Budget J-Books/FY27/Army/RDTE - Vol 3 - Budget Activity 5A.pdf$$, 210, $$2026-05-07T23:10:23.471687+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0604642A$$, 2027, $$The Army's High Mobility Multipurpose Vehicle (HMMWV) is a lightweight, high performance four-wheel drive, air transportable and air droppable family of tactical
vehicles. The vehicle comes armored and unarmored with several different configurations: Command and Control; Cargo/Shelter Carrier; Weapons Carrier and
Ambulance and is capable of performing multiple mission roles for personnel and payloads across the full spectrum of military operations.

 HMMWV Occupancy Protection supports an All Belts to Seats (ABTS) effort which would mitigate occupant injuries during rollover events, integrate air bags/air belts,
 and significantly minimize head contact with the roof and doors.

 The Infantry Squad Vehicle (ISV) composed of the ISV and ISV-Utility (ISV-U) is a modified commercial off the shelf (M-COTS) program which incorporates greater
 affordability goals, as well as requirements for reduced weight, and increased vehicle transportability. The ISV provides enhanced tactical mobility for an Brigade Combat
 Team (BCT), a nine-Soldier infantry squad, with their associated equipment to move quickly around the battlefield. This includes the ability to execute medium distance
 insertion operations which provides commanders greater freedom of movement and freedom of action. The ISV-U is a five-seat ground vehicle platform that leverages
 the base ISV configuration. This provides the US Army with a highly mobile and transportable platform that provides Rapid Mission Payload capability on the proven ISV
 platform. The ISV-H is a six-seat ground vehicle platform that supports the BCT with enhanced operational flexibility by enabling air assault missions, mission command
 on the move and Tactical Operations Center (TOC) operations while providing increased payload capacity and power management capabilities to adapt to dynamic
 battle conditions. ISV deploys worldwide by sea, air, and land modes to support strategic deployment and operational maneuver in accordance with Army and Joint
 doctrine. This capability provides flexibility for entry operations (permissive and non-permissive) to counter threat anti-access strategies by using multiple austere entry
 points to bring in combined arms configured units.

 ISV, transportable by CH-47/UH-60, air drop capable, payload of nine Soldiers with equipment/supplies for three days of operations. The purpose of the ISV-U is to
 serve as cargo variant of the ISV passenger for BCTs and other end Users with larger payload. The intended function is to provide larger payload capacity and payload
 area for unique mission packages in the cargo bed across a battlefield for the User to achieve their objective. The Infantry Squad Vehicle - Heavy (ISV-H) is designed
 to fulfill critical operational roles such as export power for TOC operations and onboard power for Mission Command on the Move. These roles emphasize versatility,
 mobility, and support for tactical operations across diverse environments. Primary intended usage for the ISV-H is at Division and Brigade.

