D. Acquisition Strategy
Infantry Squad Vehicle (ISV): A firm fixed priced production contract was awarded to General Motors Defense (GMD) on 26 June 2020 following successful prototype
determination and findings from the ISV Other Transaction Authority (OTA). Army Requirements Oversight Council Memorandum (AROCM) 25-09 (30 Apr 2025)
Approved the ISV Capability Development Document Update (CDD-U), Infantry Squad Vehicle Utility (ISV- U) annex, APO increase to 5,733, and Army Acquisition
Objective (AAO) increase to 9,282. Army Requirements Oversight Council Memorandum (AROCM) 26-01 (6 Feb 2026) Approved the ISV Capability Development
Document Update (CDD-U), Infantry Squad Vehicle Utility (ISV- U) annex, APO and AAO increase to 11,582; 4,677 for ISV and 6,905 for Infantry Squad Vehicle Utility
(ISV-U).

 PD GMV will conduct a Commercial Solutions Opening (CSO) for the Infantry Squad Vehicle - Heavy (ISV-H) to evaluate industry capabilities and verify the maturity of
 technologies required to support the vehicle's development. The ISV-H requirement was validated during an Army Requirements Oversight Council in January 2026,
 and the AROC Memorandum 26-02, signed on 6 February 2026, approved the Army Acquisition Objective and Army Procurement Objective at 606 vehicles. PD GMV
 will utilize a three-segment acquisition strategy for the ISV-H. Segment 1 is divided into three subphases: Phase I, where offerors submit white paper proposals; Phase
 II, which involves discussions with offerors to refine their proposals; and Phase III, where final proposals are submitted, and awards are made up to three vendors
 with contracts to produce prototypes. Segment 2 will focus on prototype development and testing. Prototyping will emphasize Soldier Touch Points and limited safety/
 performance testing, with evaluations focusing on export power, off-road mobility, range/duration, transportability, and C5ISR onboard power. Segment 3 will leverage
 Soldier feedback and test data from Segment 2, which will be presented at a Knowledge Point to select the final vendor. Once the final vendor is selected, a production
 award will be issued to commence vehicle production.

 HMMWV Occupancy Protection: Product Director Light Tactical Vehicle (PD LTV) plans to award a STS work directive for Phase II All Belts to Seats (ABTS) on current
 STS contract. The work directive will complete additional testing and process an Engineering Change Proposal (ECP) based on the ABTS design developed and tested
 under the Phase I Task Order.




