$$, $$4ddfa59e8260c63acdf03fc84a06e4392863114047e0a7d281ab63268d24ee3e$$, $${"A": "e2d4627eb38f2e948ae6d41216644b05e7cf5852c3b8ff4b09d799dd3e933eaf", "D": "d4fdf923ba776b98bda680220afe7660b2fb7f78e25f4cb026ad0b29031d9620", "E": "e06a2832c7c1fc7a1d9b7b41096ffa5191b63d4333d417b83abb9f2604dcc930"}$$::jsonb, $$Budget J-Books/FY27/Air Force/FY27 Air Force Research, Development, Test & Evaluation  Volume II.pdf$$, 587, $$2026-05-07T23:10:02.989896+00:00$$) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0708051F$$, 2027, $$The Rapid Sustainment Modernization (RSM) program objective is to rapidly modernize sustainment practices, enhancing readiness and cutting costs by identifying,
assessing, developing, validating, verifying, and deploying cutting-edge technologies across the sustainment enterprise. This program achieves this by proactively
engaging stakeholders across the spectrum, from warfighters to depot and field maintenance teams, supply chains, and program offices, to pinpoint critical enterprise
needs. In direct support of the Secretary of War direction to increase readiness across the Department of War, efforts within this PEC will be prioritized based on the
National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA), USAF Force Design, Agile Combat Employment (ACE), and the Defense Planning Guide (DPG). These efforts will support
work and collaboration efforts across the Combat Readiness Directorate in PEs 78051F, 71212F, 72833F, 64706F, 65827F, 22834F, 52834F, 28031F, 41135F and
27521F to increase readiness across the Air Force enterprise. The program maintains flexibility to adapt to the rapidly evolving technology landscape, pivoting technical
areas and solutions as requirements, warfighter needs, and resource environments change.

 Advanced Manufacturing Program Office (AMPO) leverages innovative technologies to create superior products, refine existing ones, and cultivate advanced production
 capabilities. This strengthens manufacturing quality and processes, providing warfighters with a distinct competitive advantage. The Advanced Manufacturing (AdvM)
 program develops additive and other advanced manufacturing capabilities to produce tools, jigs, fixtures, and aircraft components, thereby mitigating diminishing
 manufacturing sources, addressing material shortages, and accelerating part procurement lead times. Repair Additive Manufacturing (RAM) technologies enhance
 maintenance capabilities, minimize downtime, and boost operational efficiency. Furthermore, the program develops deployable AdvM and RAM capabilities for contested
 environments, enabling on-demand parts and tools at the point of need, along with on-site and aircraft-side repair capabilities. Automation and Robotics (A&R) efforts
 focus on hazardous environments, material handling, and repair, assembly, and test systems. Robotic Laser Paint Removal systems exemplify this, eliminating the
 need for human presence in hazardous and confined spaces. Expeditionary Combat Technologies (ECT) develops and delivers deployable structures, power and water
 generation tools, logistics tools to reduce logistics footprints, and enhance Airmen mission effectiveness in expeditionary and austere environments. Prototyping across
 these areas facilitates the integration and demonstration of emerging technologies, accelerating their transition into warfighter capabilities through iterative development
 and increased utilization of commercial technology.

 Digital Architectures and Capabilities (DAC) is comprised of Conditioned Based Maintenance Plus (CBM+), Digital Materiel Management (DMM), and Maintenance
 Digital Ecosystem (MxDE). Conditioned Based Maintenance Plus is a collaborative Department of War readiness initiative centered on data analysis to transition
 unscheduled to scheduled maintenance, driving mission readiness improvements. It employs a failure management/data-driven decisions strategy to perform
 predictive/proactive maintenance, leveraging Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning (AI/ML) capabilities to identify evidence of need to perform maintenance. Sensor
 based algorithms leverage AI/ML to transform onboard sensor data into component degradation detection alerts, enabling decision advantage. Predictive Analytics

 and Decision Assistant (PANDA) serves as the enterprise AI/ML software platform for data analytics and visualization. Digital Materiel Management is a materiel
 management ecosystem powered by Always Guaranteeing Operationally Ready Aircraft (AGORA), a cloud-based ecosystem of enterprise AdvM and DMM engineering
 software capabilities that enable Department of Air Force (DAF) stakeholders to leverage AdvM technologies to solve supply chain challenges and improve aircraft
 readiness, AM Innovation Hub is a cloud-based platform for innovation and collaboration, facilitating the sharing of AM projects and files, SEEKR is a tool that provides
 program offices the ability to identify viable part candidates, and Part Assessment and Cost Tool (PACT) provides a decision support framework, helping program offices
 assess the feasibility of using additive manufacturing (AM) technologies to overcome complex supply chain problems. The MxDE leverages Lighthouse Integration
 Technology Engine (LITE) to integrate developmental, operational, and legacy Air Force Logistics information technology (IT) platforms within a hub-and-spoke
 framework modernizing USAF systems enabling disparate data to be displayed through a single pane of glass, driving decision advantage.

 Funding in this PE supports agile development activities that rapidly address emergent requirements from the DAF enterprise during the year of execution. These may
 include addressing Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages, reducing unscheduled weapons system maintenance, and enabling maintenance
 capabilities in austere environments. The program may fund studies of new technologies to determine their applicability to DAF requirements.

 This program element included all necessary expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds would be in
 addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 0605829F, 0605831F, 0605833F, and 0605898F

 This requirement supports performance of full financial audit as required by title 10 U.S.C. Chapter 9A, Sec 240-D.

 This effort is in Budget Activity 4, Advanced Component Development and Prototypes (ACD&P), because efforts are necessary to evaluate integrated technologies,
 representative modes or prototype systems in a high fidelity and realistic operating environment.$$, $$The Rapid Sustainment Modernization (RSM) program objective is to rapidly modernize sustainment practices, enhancing readiness and cutting costs by identifying,
