Title: CON-IT System Development                                                                                                        28.088      28.876        25.815
Description: CON-IT development is accomplished using agile software development practices to build upon a Government-
off-the-Shelf contract management system to replace four legacy contract writing systems and multiple support systems.
Development efforts are phased into eight major capabilities according to the requirements of each contracting community. This
enables phased transitions from the various legacy systems to CON-IT. Capabilities are fielded utilizing the Minimum Viable
Product (MVP) concept for each user group. The MVP contains the minimum set of requirements users need to complete their
mission. The deployed MVP is then continually enhanced and refined in future capability releases. Thus far, the Department of
the Air Force (DAF) fielded MVP Capabilities 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 and deployed CON-IT to the operational/installation, contingency
contracting, and Weapon Systems communities. Capability 7 is in work.

In FY2025, the DAF delivered CON-IT to 2244 ConWrite and 511 Automated Contract Preparation System (ACPS) users via
swivel chair integration, in which both new and legacy systems are used concurrently. This brought the total number of active
users to 6,970. Additional users will be added as capabilities are developed, including additional classified users and E-Filing
users in FY2026.

