Minimum Viable Product (MVP): Only essential functionality that solves a core user problem, often called the "minimum feature set". The product must work well enough
to be usable and provide value to early adopters. Capability MVP end dates do not mark end of capability development.
- Research and Development (R&D) MVP (Capability 6) delivery was accelerated to 1QFY2026, four months ahead of the original schedule, to accelerate the sunsetting
of the legacy ConWrite system.
- E-Filing MVP (Capability 7) delivery was adjusted by four months (to 3QFY2026) due to reprioritizing resources for accelerated R&D MVP delivery and revised E-Filing
MVP scope.
- Continuous Capability Development continues to implement new capabilities post MVP deliveries, supports contract migration from legacy systems, and maintains
system compliance with modern data standards, Department of War (DoW) mandates, and auditability objectives.




